          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-justify">
            Special Technology Zones Authority (STZA) is an autonomous body established under the Cabinet Division,
            Government of Pakistan, with the Honorable Prime Minister of Pakistan as the President of the Board of
            Governors (BoG) of the Authority.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-justify">
            STZA has been mandated to promote the knowledge-based innovation ecosystem through the establishment of
            Special Technology Zones (STZs) across the country. STZA aims to provide institutional and legislative
            support for the technology sector by providing fiscal and forex incentives under STZA Act 2021, to attract
            foreign direct investments, incentivize futuristic entrepreneurship, enable job creation, and commercialize
            technological knowledge.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-blue-100 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-[#3674B5]">
            <p class="text-gray-800 font-semibold">
              <i class="fas fa-certificate text-[#3674B5] mr-2"></i>
              On August 31, 2022, STZA issued zone notification to the University of Agriculture Faisalabad as
              Pakistan's 1st AgriTech Park.
            </p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-justify text-sm">
            The University of Agriculture Faisalabad has been notified for zone developer to develop, operate and
            managing infrastructure inside STZ. In addition to existing infrastructure at the main campus, the
            University has sufficient land measuring 200 acres in Faisalabad (about 3 KM from M-4 CPEC Route) for Zone
            Infrastructure Development of AgriTech Park.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

